My husband and I ordered here for lunch for the first time today. I was pleasantly surprised by how fresh and high-quality the food was! I've read some of the negative reviews, which is why we haven't ordered here before, but I must say, the two lunch specials we got today were just fantastic. We ordered the orange chicken and kung pao chicken, both with fried rice (egg rolls included). The egg rolls were super fresh, and tasted like they had a little chinese five spice inside. Our chicken dishes were both amazing - the kung pao was spicy and tender, with crunchy zucchini and peppers. The orange chicken was still hot and crispy, even after our 10 minute walk home in the cold. We'll definitely be back!

I was very dissatisfied with my experience. I ordered the chicken fried rice and it took an extremely long time to come out, and there was only one other customer. But the wait was nowhere near the worst part.  While i waited for my food i had plenty of time to soak up Eat First's atmosphere. The walls were peeling and had huge ugly cracks in them and the floors looked like they haven't been cleaned in 7 and a half years.  The food finally arrived about 45 minutes later, and boy let me tell you. It was the absolute worst chicken fried rice I've ever tasted. The rice was almost crunchy, it was pretty cold, and the chicken did not look or taste like it was cooked correctly. I don't know how you can mess up something so simple after taking 45 minutes to do so.  I recommend the place change their name to "Eat Last" because that's where they sit on my list of places to eat.

This was by far the most disappointing Chinese I've ever ordered. Most of it ended up in the trash. The orange beef was swimming in so much sauce that it was just soggy mush. The sauce described as spicy was anything but... I suspect that the reddish orange substance I found splashed and smeared all over the inside of the bag may have been a pepper paste to spice it up... however scraping the bag didn't seem worth the effort for this mess. The pan fried dumplings.... maybe they were pan fried once but they tasted more like they'd been microwaved. You know that taste and texture that happens when you put something doughy in the micro, yuck! There were no napkins or plastic ware included. Even the delivery which I read great reviews about was slow and well outside of my delivery window. Maybe they were just having an off night but I certainly won't be taking the risk to find out.
